INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4700','letter','1767-04-11','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Henry','Home','','individual','','In the same session with the stamp act, an act was passed to regulate the quartering of soldiers in America','ltr_ben4700.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4701','letter','1767-04-11','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Ross','','individual','','Here public affairs are in great disorder; a strong opposition against the ministry, which, at the same time, is thought not to be well united; and daily apprehensions of new changes make it extremely difficult to get forward with business.','ltr_ben4701.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4702','letter','1767-05-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Cadwallader','Evans','','individual','','I thank you for your remarks on the gout. They may be useful to me, who have already had some touches of that distemper.','ltr_ben4702.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4703','letter','1767-06-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Galloway','','individual','','In my last of May 2Oth, I mentioned my hopes that we should at length get over all obstructions to the repeal of the act restraining the legal tender of paper money; but those hopes are now greatly lessened.','ltr_ben4703.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4704','letter','1767-06-17','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Mary','Stevenson','','individual','','A Muse, you must know, visited me this Morning! I see you are surpriz\'d, as I was. I never saw one before. And shall never see another.','ltr_ben4704.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4705','letter','1767-06-22','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','It seems now as if I should stay here another Winter, and therefore I must leave it to your Judgment to act in the Affair of your Daughter\'s Match, as shall seem best.','ltr_ben4705.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4706','letter','1767-07-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Peter','Collinson','','individual','','I have heard of an account you lately received from Russia of some discovery of an ancient sepulchre in the frontiers of that country.','ltr_ben4706.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4707','letter','1767-07-17','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Franklin','','individual','','I find here but two of our relations remaining, that bear the name of Franklin, viz. Thomas Franklin of Lutterworth in Leicestershire, a dyer, and his daughter Sally Franklin','ltr_ben4707.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4708','letter','1767-08-01','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Richard','Price','','individual','','Last night I received a letter from D r Robertson, acquainting me that the University of Edinburgh have on my recommendation conferred the degree of D r in Divinity upon the Rev d M r Cooper of Boston','ltr_ben4708.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4709','letter','1767-08-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','I have now before me all your late Letters, and shall answer them Article by Article.','ltr_ben4709.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4710','letter','1767-08-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','George','Croghan','','individual','','I return you many thanks for the box of elephants\' tusks and grinders. They are extremely curious on many accounts','ltr_ben4710.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4711','letter','1767-08-08','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Galloway','','individual','','The confusion among our great men still continues as much as ever, and a melancholy thing it is to consider, that, instead of employing the present leisure of peace in such measures as might extend our commerce','ltr_ben4711.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4712','letter','1767-08-25','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Canton','','individual','','When I was at Paris about 10 Days since, I was told that a Comet was then visible with a Tail of considerable Length.','ltr_ben4712.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4713','letter','1767-08-28','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','Last week I dined at Lord Shelburne\'s, and had a long conversation with him and Mr. Conway (there being no other company) on the subject of reducing American expense.','ltr_ben4713.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4714','letter','1767-09-14','Paris','','FRA','Benjamin','Franklin','','Mary','Stevenson','','individual','','Soon after I left you in that agreable Society at Bromley, I took the Resolution of making a Trip with Sir John Pringle into France.','ltr_ben4714.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4715','letter','1767-11-25','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','I wish the Boston people had been as quiet, since Governor Bernard has sent over all their violent papers to the ministry, and wrote them word that he daily expected a rebellion.','ltr_ben4715.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4716','letter','1767-11-27','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Canton','','individual','','After the Society was gone, my Lord Moreton said (when I offered him the Paper) that it ought to have been deliver\'d before and read to the Society: he however desir\'d me to produce it to the Council.','ltr_ben4716.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4717','letter','1767-12-01','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Galloway','','individual','','I am inclined to think with you that the small sum you have issued to discharge the public debts only will not be materially affected in its credit for want of the legal tender, considering especially the present extreme want of money in the province.','ltr_ben4717.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4718','letter','1767-12-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Ross','','individual','','The instruction you mention, as proposed by a certain great man, was really a wild one. The reasons you made use of against it were clear and strong, and could not but prevail.','ltr_ben4718.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4719','letter','1767-12-19','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','The resolutions of the Boston people concerning trade make a great noise here. Parliament has not yet taken notice of them, but the newspapers are in full cry against America.','ltr_ben4719.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4720','letter','1768-01-09','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','We have had so many alarms of changes, which did not take place, that just when I wrote it was thought the ministry would stand their ground.','ltr_ben4720.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4721','letter','1768-01-09','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Galloway','','individual','','I wrote to you via Boston, and have little to add, except to acquaint you that some changes have taken place since my last, which have not the most promising aspect for America','ltr_ben4721.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4722','letter','1768-01-31','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','P','Berthier','','individual','','With cordial Thanks for your many Civilities to me when in Paris, I take this Opportunity of acquainting you, that your Certificate has been received by the Royal Society','ltr_ben4722.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4723','letter','1768-01-31','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas Francois','Dalibard','','individual','','I sent you some time since, Priestly\'s History of Electricity, under the Care of Mr. Molini, Bookseller on the Quay des Augustins. I hope it got safe to Paris, and that you have receiv\'d it.','ltr_ben4723.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4724','letter','1768-02-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','I have received also the Indian and buckwheat meal, that they brought from you, with the apples, cranberries, and nuts, for all which I thank you. They all prove good','ltr_ben4724.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4725','letter','1768-02-17','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Galloway','','individual','','In mine of January 9, I wrote to you that I believed, notwithstanding the clamour against America had been greatly increased by the Boston proceedings, we should attempt this session to obtain the repeal of the restraining act relating to paper money.','ltr_ben4725.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4726','letter','1768-02-20','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Cadwallader','Evans','','individual','','In yours of November 20th, you mention the lead in the worms of stills as a probable cause of the dry belly-ache among punch-drinkers in our West Indies.','ltr_ben4726.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4727','letter','1768-02-20','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Livezey','','individual','','your kind letter of Nov. 18, with a very welcome present of another Dozen of your wine. The former has been found excellent by many good judges, my Wine Merchant in particular was very desirous of knowing what quantity of it might be had','ltr_ben4727.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4728','letter','1768-02-20','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Wharton','','individual','','The story you mention of secretary Conway\'s wondering what I could be doing in England, and that he had not seen me for a considerable time, savours strongly of the channel through which it came, and deserves no notice.','ltr_ben4728.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4729','letter','1768-02-28','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Henry','Home','','individual','','I have long been of an opinion similar to that you express, and think happiness consists more in small conveniences or pleasures that occur every day, than in great pieces of good fortune that happen but seldom to a man in the course of his life.','ltr_ben4729.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4730','letter','1768-03-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Galloway','','individual','','The old Parliament is gone, and its enemies now find themselves at liberty to abuse it. I inclose you a pamphlet, published the very hour of its prorogation.','ltr_ben4730.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4731','letter','1768-03-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','The purpose of settling the new colonies seems at present to be dropped, the change of American administration not appearing favourable to it. There seems rather to be an inclination to abandon the posts in the back country as more expensive than useful','ltr_ben4731.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4732','letter','1768-03-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','group','To The Committee Of Correspondence In Pennsylvania','On receipt of your letter of January 20, Mr. Jackson and myself waited on Lord Hillsborough, the new secretary of state for American affairs, and communicated to him the contents','ltr_ben4732.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4733','letter','1768-04-16','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','group','To The Committee Of Correspondence In Pennsylvania','I have just received your favour of February 20, directed to Mr. Jackson and myself, containing instructions for our conduct relating to the application for a repeal of the duty act, to the change of government, and to the legal tender of paper money','ltr_ben4733.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4734','letter','1768-04-16','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','nothing has been talked or thought of here but elections. There have been amazing contests all over the kingdom, twenty or thirty thousand pounds of a side spent in several places, and inconceivable mischief done','ltr_ben4734.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4735','letter','1768-05-10','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Pringle','','individual','','You may remember, that when we were travelling together in Holland you remarked, that the trackschuyt in one of the stages went slower than usual, and inquired of the boatman, what might be the reason','ltr_ben4735.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4736','letter','1768-05-14','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Ross','','individual','','I received your favour of March 13th, and am extremely concerned at the disorders on our frontiers, and at the debility or wicked connivance of our government and magistrates,','ltr_ben4736.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4737','letter','1768-05-14','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Galloway','','individual','','While I am writing, a great mob of coal porters fills the street, carrying a wretch of their business upon poles to be ducked, and otherwise punished at their pleasure for working at the old wages.','ltr_ben4737.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4738','letter','1768-07-02','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Winthrop','','individual','','You must needs think the time long that your instruments have been in hand. Sundry circumstances have occasioned the delay.','ltr_ben4738.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4739','letter','1768-07-02','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','Instead of my being appointed to a new office, there has been a motion made to deprive me of that I now hold, and, I believe, for the same reason, though that was not the reason given out, viz. my being too much of an American','ltr_ben4739.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4740','letter','1768-07-02','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Galloway','','individual','','My Lord Clare took me home from court to dine with him but two days before, saying he should be without other company, and wanted to talk with me on sundry American businesses.','ltr_ben4740.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4741','letter','1768-07-25','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','C','Dumas','','individual','','As you seem only to have seen Extracts in the Magazines from the Account of East Florida, I send you the Book itself, which may afford you some farther Lights concerning the Country.','ltr_ben4741.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4742','letter','1768-07-28','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Barbeu','Dubourg','','individual','','the new method of treating the small-pox, which you call the tonic or bracing method; I will take occasion from it to mention a practice to which I have accustomed myself.','ltr_ben4742.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4743','letter','1768-07-28','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Du Pont','De Nemours','','individual','','I RECEIVED your obliging letter of the 10th May, with the most acceptable present of your Physiocratie, which I have read with great pleasure, and received from it a great deal of instruction.','ltr_ben4743.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4744','letter','1768-08-09','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Alleyne','','individual','','You made an Apology to me for not acquaint\' me sooner with your Marriage. I ought now to make an Apology to you for delaying so long the Answer to your Letter.','ltr_ben4744.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4745','letter','1768-08-09','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','David','Hall','','individual','','I have wrote my Mind fully to you in former Letters relating to the Stamp Act; so that I have but little to add, except what you desire to know about the 2 on Advertisements.','ltr_ben4745.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4746','letter','1768-08-18','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','position','Printer Of The London Chronicle','QUERIES, recommended to the Consideration of those Gentlemen who are for vigorous measures with the Americans.','ltr_ben4746.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4747','letter','1768-08-25','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','position','Printer Of The London Public Advertiser','Contractors, jobbing mercantile members of parliament, officers starving on half pay, and gunsmiths who toast, as the papers tell us, a speedy and a perpetual war, may wish, rather than no war at all, for a civil one in America.','ltr_ben4747.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4748','letter','1768-09-21','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Giambatista','Beccaria','','individual','','The bearer of my letter is Monsieur L\'Epinasse my good friend who is an ingenious electrician, one of the most excellent that we have.','ltr_ben4748.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4749','letter','1768-10-21','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Crowley','','individual','','As you have printed here your letter of yesterday to your friend in America, and it may be long before you receive an answer from thence, permit me in the mean time to give you a few remarks on it, submitting them, as you have done your Letter, to the Public.','ltr_ben4749.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4750','letter','1768-10-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','It feels very strange to me to have Ships and Packets come in, and no Letters from you. But I do not complain of it, because I know the reason is, my having written to you that I was coming home.','ltr_ben4750.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4751','letter','1768-10-28','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Mary','Stevenson','','I see very clearly the Unhappiness of your Situation, and that it does not arise from any Fault in you. I pity you most sincerely. I should not, however, have thought of giving you Advice on this Occasion, if you had not requested it','','description','ltr_ben4751.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4752','letter','1768-11-28','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','individual','','Your sentiments of the importance of the present dispute between Great Britain and the colonies appear to me extremely just. There is nothing I wish for more, than to see it amicably and equitably settled.','ltr_ben4752.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4753','letter','1768-12-21','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','I am made by this to apprehend that something is amiss, and perhaps have more Uneasiness from the Uncertainty, than I should have had if you had told me what it was.','ltr_ben4753.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4754','letter','1769-01-01','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Henry','Home','','individual','','I am glad to find you are turning your thoughts to political subjects, and particularly to those of money, taxes, manufactures, and commerce. The world is yet much in the dark on these important points','ltr_ben4754.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4755','letter','1769-01-09','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Bartram','','individual','','I received your kind letter of November 5th, and the box directed to the King is since come to hand.','ltr_ben4755.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4756','letter','1769-01-31','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Jean Baptiste','Le Roy','','individual','','The Farmer\'s Letters were written by one Mr. Dickinson, of Philadelphia, and not by me, as you seem to suppose. I only caused them to be reprinted here with that little Preface, and had no other hand in them','ltr_ben4756.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4757','letter','1769-02-21','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Henry','Home','','individual','','I received your excellent paper on the preferable use of oxen in agriculture, and have put it in the way of being communicated to the public here.','ltr_ben4757.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4758','letter','1769-02-24','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Cooper','','individual','','I was about to return home last Summer, and had some thoughts of doing it by way of Boston; but the untoward Situation of American Affairs here induc\'d my Friends to advise my staying another Winter.','ltr_ben4758.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4759','letter','1769-03-00','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Winthrop','','individual','','At length after much Delay and Difficulty I have been able to obtain your Telescope, that was made by Mr. Short before his Death. His brother who succeeds in the Business has fitted it up and compleated it.','ltr_ben4759.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4760','letter','1769-04-27','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Cooper','','individual','','The Parliament remain fix\'d in their Resolution not to repeal the Duty Acts this Session, and will rise next Tuesday. I hope my Country folks will remain as fix\'d in their Resolutions of Industry and Frugality till these Acts are repeal\'d.','ltr_ben4760.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4761','letter','1769-04-27','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Jane','Mecom','','individual','','I am now grown too old to be ambitious of such a station, as that which you say has been mentioned to you.','ltr_ben4761.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4762','letter','1769-05-09','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','position','Printer Of The London Chronicle','While the public attention is so much turned towards America, every letter from thence that promises new information, is pretty generally read.','ltr_ben4762.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4763','letter','1769-06-27','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Mary','Stevenson','','individual','','Agreable to your Orders, delivered to me very punctually by Temple, I return you enclosed Voltaire\'s Verses. The Translation I think full as good as the Original.','ltr_ben4763.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4764','letter','1769-07-09','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','group','Committee Of Merchants In Philadelphia','The letter was published, and universally spoken well of, as a well written, sensible, manly, and spirited performance; and I believe the publication has been of service to our cause.','ltr_ben4764.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4765','letter','1769-07-09','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Bartram','','individual','','you may yet be very useful to your country and to mankind, if you sit down quietly at home, digest the knowledge you have acquired, and compile and publish the many observations you have made','ltr_ben4765.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4766','letter','1769-07-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','James','Bowdoin','','individual','','I am honoured with yours of May 10th, and agree with you perfectly in your sentiments of public affairs. Government here seems now to be growing more moderate with regard to America','ltr_ben4766.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4767','letter','1769-09-02','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Mary','Stevenson','','individual','','JUST come home from a Venison Feast, where I have drank more than a Philosopher ought, I find my dear Polly\'s chearful, chatty Letter, that exhilirates me more than all the Wine.','ltr_ben4767.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4768','letter','1769-09-07','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Cadwallader','Evans','','individual','','I gave them immediately to Mr. Maskelyne, the Astronomer Royal, who will compare and digest the whole received from different parts of the world, and report thereon to the Royal Society.','ltr_ben4768.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4769','letter','1769-09-22','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Barbeu','Dubourg','','individual','','With this you will receive some Sheets of the Piece now printing, and which I am promised shall be finish\'d in a few Days. I am afraid it is not so correct as it should be','ltr_ben4769.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4770','letter','1769-09-22','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Dalibard','','individual','','I embrace it to thank you most heartily for the many Civilities & Marks of Friendship I received from you & Mad. Dalibard, while in Paris','ltr_ben4770.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4771','letter','1769-09-03','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Cooper','','individual','','I am just returned from France, where I found our Dispute much attended to, several of our Pamphlets being translated and printed there','ltr_ben4771.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4772','letter','1769-10-29','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Anthony','Todd','','individual','','Discoursing with Captain Folger, a very intelligent Mariner of the Island of Nantucket, in New England, concerning the long Passages made by some ships bound from England to New York, I received from him the following Information','ltr_ben4772.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4773','letter','1769-00-00','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Mary','Stevenson','','individual','','I have received the Garters you have so kindly knit for me ; they are of the only Sort that I can wear, having worn none of any kind for 20 Years, till you began to supply me; but besides their Usefulness, these appear to me the finest, neatest, and prettiest that were ever made !','ltr_ben4773.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4774','letter','1769-11-29','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','W','Strahan','','individual','','I find yours of the 22 d , containing a number of Queries, that would require a Pamphlet to answer them fully. You, however, desire only brief Answers, which I shall endeavour to give you.','ltr_ben4774.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4775','letter','1770-01-00','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Bartram','','individual','','I cannot make you adequate returns in kind ; but I send you however some of the true rhubarb seed, which you desire.','ltr_ben4775.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4776','letter','1770-01-22','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Mary','Stevenson','','individual','','Your good Mother has complained more of her Head since you left us than ever before. If she stoops, or looks, or bends her Neck downwards, on any occasion, it is with great Pain and Difficulty, that she gets her Head up again.','ltr_ben4776.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4777','letter','1770-02-12','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Nevil','Maskelyne','','individual','','I have just received a letter from Mr. Winthrop, dated December 7th, containing the following account','ltr_ben4777.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4778','letter','1770-02-16','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Viny','','individual','','I can easily conceive the Difficulty a Man in your Situation, with such Connections, and so well esteemed and belov\'d among them, must have in resolving to leave them with an Intention of Settling in a distant Country.','ltr_ben4778.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4779','letter','1770-03-17','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Michael','Hillegas','','individual','','have made inquiries, as you desired, concerning the copper covering of houses. It has been used here in a few instances only, and the practice does not seem to gain ground.','ltr_ben4779.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4780','letter','1770-03-18','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','individual','','But, though both the Duke of Grafton and Lord North were and are, in my opinion, rather inclined to satisfy us, yet the Bedford party are so violent against us, and so prevalent in the council, that more moderate measures could not take place.','ltr_ben4780.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4781','letter','1770-04-14','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Cooper','','individual','','All Europe is attentive to the Dispute between Britain and the Colonies, & I own I have a Satisfaction in seeing, that our Part is taken Everywhere','ltr_ben4781.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4782','letter','1770-05-31','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Mary','Stevenson','','individual','','I write this Line just to say, that I am sure you are a much better Judge in this Affair of your own, than I can possibly be.','ltr_ben4782.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4783','letter','1770-06-06','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Jonathan','Williams','','individual','','If I could have given you any intimation of the intentions of government with regard to America, that might be depended upon, you should have had them in good time for use','ltr_ben4783.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4784','letter','1770-06-08','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Cooper','','individual','','As to the Standing Army kept up among us in time of Peace, without the Consent of our Assemblies, I am clearly of Opinion that it is not agreable to the Constitution.','ltr_ben4784.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4785','letter','1770-06-08','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Franklin','','individual','','I was happy to find that neither you, nor any of your family, were in the way of those murderers. I hope that before this time the town is quite freed from such dangerous and mischievous inmates.','ltr_ben4785.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4786','letter','1770-06-10','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','As to myself, I had from Christmas till Easter, a disagreable Giddiness hanging about me, which however did not hinder me from being about and doing Business.','ltr_ben4786.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4787','letter','1770-06-26','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Rhoads','','individual','','It appears to me of great Importance to build our DwellingHouses, if we can, in a Manner more secure from Danger by Fire.','ltr_ben4787.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4788','letter','1770-07-24','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Mary','Hewson','','individual','','I am apt to love everybody that loves you, and therefore I suppose I shall in time love your new Mother, and new Sister, and your new Dolly. ','ltr_ben4788.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4789','letter','1770-08-27','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Ewing','','individual','','I received your Favour of June 14, with several Copies of your Observations of the Transit of Venus, for which I thank you.','ltr_ben4789.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4790','letter','1770-08-27','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Cadwallader','Evans','','individual','','Thanks for the books on the silk affair. It will give me great pleasure to see that business brought to perfection among us.','ltr_ben4790.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4791','letter','1770-09-22','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','position','Publisher Of Craven Street Gazette','It is whispered, that the new family administration, which took place on her Majesty\'s departure, promises, like all other new administrations, to govern much better than the old one.','ltr_ben4791.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4792','letter','1770-00-00','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','position','Publisher Of Craven Street Gazette','I make no doubt of the Truth of what the Papers tell us, that a certain great Person is half-starved on the Blade-Bone of a Sheep (I cannot call it of Mutton, there being none on it)','ltr_ben4792.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4793','letter','1770-10-02','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Barbeu','Dubourg','','individual','','We only assert, that, having Parliaments of our own, and not having representatives in that of Great Britain, our Parliaments are the only judges of what we can and what we ought to contribute','ltr_ben4793.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4794','letter','1770-10-02','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Du Pont','De Nemours','','individual','','I purpose returning to America in the ensuing Summer, if our Disputes should be adjusted, as I hope they will be in the next Session of Parliament.','ltr_ben4794.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4795','letter','1770-10-03','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','I am glad your little Grandson recovered so soon of his Illness, as I see you are quite in Love with him, and your Happiness wrapt up in his','ltr_ben4795.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4796','letter','1770-12-24','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Gushing','','individual','','Your favour of October 31st came to hand a few days since, with the vote of the House of Representatives appointing me their agent here, which, as it was unsolicited on my part, I esteem the greater honour','ltr_ben4796.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4797','letter','1770-12-30','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Cooper','','individual','','I esteem the Appointment to the Agency of your Province, unexpected and unsolicited by me, as one of the greatest Honours for which I must think myself indebted to your Friendship.','ltr_ben4797.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4798','letter','1770-12-30','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Jane','Mecom','','individual','','As to the Rumor you mention, (which was, as Josiah tells me, that I had been deprived of my Place in the PostOffice on account of a Letter I wrote to Philadelphia,) it might have this Foundation','ltr_ben4798.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4799','letter','1771-02-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Gushing','','individual','','The doctrine of the right of Parliament to lay taxes on America is now almost generally given up here, and one seldom meets in conversation with any, who continue to assert it.','ltr_ben4799.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4800','letter','1771-02-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','James','Bowdoin','','individual','','I am very sensible of the honour done me by your House of Representatives, in appointing me their Agent here. It will make me extreamly happy, if I can render them any valuable Service.','ltr_ben4800.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4801','letter','1771-02-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Cooper','','individual','','In the same Confidence I send you the inclosed Extract from my Journal, containing a late Conference between the Secretary and your Friend, in which you will see a little of his Temper','ltr_ben4801.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4802','letter','1771-02-10','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Cadwallader','Evans','','individual','','I have not now before me your letter, which came with the sample of silk, having put it into the hands of Mr. Walpole with the sample, who has promised me full and particular answers to all your queries, after the silk has been thoroughly examined.','ltr_ben4802.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4803','letter','1771-02-10','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Rhoads','','individual','','I am glad to hear that you have good Workmen in the Stucco Way, and that it is likely to take place of Wainscot.','ltr_ben4803.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4804','letter','1771-03-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Robert','Morris','','individual','','Notwithstanding the ample Recommendations brought over by M r Winter, the Bishop of London has refused him Ordination, for two Reasons, as I understand, his mechanical Education, and his Connection with M r Whitefield & the Methodists.','ltr_ben4804.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4805','letter','1771-03-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Jonathan','Williams','','individual','','I suppose Jonathan has told you, that the lottery is drawn, and your two new tickets had the same success as the former, namely, one twenty-pound prize, and one blank. Would you go on any further?','ltr_ben4805.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4806','letter','1771-03-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','RECIPIENT FIRST','Williams','','individual','','I received your kind Letter with your Sons. They are, I assure you, exceeding welcome to me ; and they behave with so much Prudence, that no two young Men could possibly less need the Advice you would have me give them.','ltr_ben4806.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4807','letter','1771-04-20','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','The Board are not favourably disposed towards your Insolvent Acts, pretending to doubt whether distant Creditors, particularly such as reside in England, may not sometimes be injured by them.','ltr_ben4807.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4808','letter','1771-04-22','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Humphrey','Marshall','','individual','','It gave me Pleasure to hear, that tho\' the Merchants had departed from their Agreement of NonImportation, the Spirit of Industry and Frugality was likely to continue among the People.','ltr_ben4808.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4809','letter','1771-05-15','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','group','Committee Of Correspondence In Massachusetts','I think one may clearly see, in the system of customs to be exacted in America by act of Parliament, the seeds sown of a total disunion of the two countries, though, as yet, that event may be at a considerable distance.','ltr_ben4809.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4810','letter','1771-05-17','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Isaac','Smith','','individual','','A good general Rule in travelling foreign Countries, is, to avoid as much as possible all Disputes, & to be contented with such Provisions and Cookery, as you meet with in the Inns','ltr_ben4810.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4811','letter','1771-06-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','The Joy was in a fair way of being doubled on the same Day, for the Queen was deliver\' d early this Morning of another Prince, the eighth Child, there being now six Princes and two Princesses, all lovely Children.','ltr_ben4811.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4812','letter','1771-06-10','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Cushing','','individual','','All Views or Expectations of drawing any considerable Revenue to this Country from the Colonies are, I believe, generally given over, and it seems probable that nothing of that kind will ever again be attempted.','ltr_ben4812.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4813','letter','1771-06-24','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Jonathan','Shipley','','individual','','I have taken the Liberty of sending by the Southampton Stage, which goes to-morrow, a Parcel directed to your Lordship, to be left at the Turnpike next beyond Winchester, containing one of my Books for Miss Georgiana','ltr_ben4813.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4814','letter','1771-07-03','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Wimberly','Jones','','individual','','I see by the newspapers that your new Assembly is also dissolved. I am sorry for these differences, which must be uncomfortable to you and all that wish the welfare of the province.','ltr_ben4814.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4815','letter','1771-07-04','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Cadwallader','Evans','','individual','','I was disappointed till lately, when I had a meeting with Mr. Patterson, esteemed one of the best judges of that commodity, who favoured me with the enclosed paper, and, in conversation, with the following particulars.','ltr_ben4815.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4816','letter','1771-07-12','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Franklin','','individual','','Yesterday a very odd accident happened, which I must mention to you, as it relates to your grandfather.','ltr_ben4816.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4817','letter','1771-07-17','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Bartram','','individual','','As to your pension, there is not, I believe, the least reason for you to apprehend its being stopped. I know not who receives it for you here, or I should quicken them in writing to you.','ltr_ben4817.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4818','letter','1771-07-18','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Cadwallader','Evans','','individual','','The European silk I understand is all yellow, and most of the India silk. What comes from China is white.','ltr_ben4818.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4819','letter','1771-07-25','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Johnathan','Shipley','','individual','','I SHOULD have been happy in accompanying your Lordship on that agreable Party, or in being at Twyford instead of this dusty Town; but Business kept me here longer than I expected.','ltr_ben4819.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4820','letter','1771-08-14','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','I am glad to hear of all your Welfares, and that the Pictures &c. were safe arrived. You do not tell me who mounted the great one, nor where you have hung it up.','ltr_ben4820.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4821','letter','1771-10-27','Edinburgh','','SCT','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Strahan','','individual','','But that excellent Christian David Hume, agreable to the Precepts of the Gospel, has received the Stranger, and I now live with him at his House in the new Town most happily.','ltr_ben4821.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4822','letter','1771-11-17','Edinburgh','','SCT','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Strahan','','individual','','I have been at Blair Drummond on a visit to my friend Lord Kames, thence I went to Glasgow, thence to Carron Works, viewing the Canal by the way.','ltr_ben4822.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4823','letter','1771-11-25','Preston','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Mary','Hewson','','individual','','I thank you for your Intelligence about my Godson. I believe you are sincere, when you say you think him as fine a Child as you wish to see.','ltr_ben4823.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4824','letter','1772-01-00','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Alexander','Dick','','individual','','My last Expedition convinced me that I grow too old for Rambling, and that \'twas probable I should never make such another Journey.','ltr_ben4824.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4825','letter','1772-01-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Jane','Mecom','','individual','','I have now been some weeks returned from my journey through Wales, Ireland, Scotland, and the North of England, which, besides being an agreeable tour with a pleasant companion, has contributed to the establishment of my health','ltr_ben4825.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4826','letter','1772-01-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','','','group','Committee Of Correspondence In Massachusetts','The town now begins to fill with members of Parliament, and great officers of state coming in daily to celebrate the Queen\'s birthday, and be present at the opening of the session','ltr_ben4826.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4827','letter','1772-01-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Cooper','','individual','','The Attempt to get the Commissioners exempted from the Payment of their Taxes, by an Instruction to the Governor, is the most indiscrete Thing, surely, to say nothing of its Injustice','ltr_ben4827.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4828','letter','1772-01-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','James','Bowdoin','','individual','','The Governing of Colonies by Instructions has long been a favourite Point with Ministers here.','ltr_ben4828.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4829','letter','1772-01-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joshua','Babcock','','individual','','I have lately made a Tour thro\' Ireland and Scotland. In those Countries a small Part of the Society are Landlords, great Noblemen, and Gentlemen, extreamly opulent, living in the highest Affluence and Magnificence','ltr_ben4829.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4830','letter','1772-01-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Gushing','','individual','','Tho\' my Constitution, and too great Confinement to Business during the Winter, seem to require the Air and Exercise of a long Journey once a Year, which I have now practised for more than 20 Years past, yet I should not have been out so long this Time','ltr_ben4830.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4831','letter','1772-01-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Samuel','Franklin','','individual','','I knew a wise old Man, who us\'d to advise his young Friends to chuse Wives out of a Bunch ; for where there were many Daughters, he said they improv\'d each other, and from Emulation acquired more Accomplishments','ltr_ben4831.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4832','letter','1772-01-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Ezra','Styles','','individual','','There is no doubt of its being a genuine Translation of the Books at present deem\'d sacred as the Writings of Zoroaster by his Followers','ltr_ben4832.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4833','letter','1772-01-28','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','I am much pleas\'d with your little Histories of our Grand son, & happy in thinking how much Amusement he must afford you. I pray that God may continue him to us','ltr_ben4833.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4834','letter','1772-01-28','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Anthony','Tissington','','individual','','I received your very kind Letter of the i5\' h together with the Turkey, which prov\'d exceeding fine. We regal\'d a Number of our Friends with it','ltr_ben4834.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4835','letter','1772-01-29','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Sarah','Bache','','individual','','You might easily learn Accounts, and you can copy Letters, or write them very well upon Occasion. By Industry & Frugality you may get forward in the World, being both of you yet young.','ltr_ben4835.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4836','letter','1772-01-30','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','At Dublin we saw and were entertained by both Parties, the Courtiers & the Patriots. The latter treated me with particular Respect.','ltr_ben4836.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4837','letter','1772-02-04','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Foxcroft','','individual','','It is a common Error in Friends when they would extol their Friend, to make Comparisons & to depreciate the Merits of others.','ltr_ben4837.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4838','letter','1772-02-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Bond','','individual','','I suppose your Son Richard will spend some time in London, where by what I have heard, Physic and Surgery may be studied to as great Advantage as in any Part of the World, by Attending the Anatomical Lectures','ltr_ben4838.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4839','letter','1772-02-06','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Cadwallader','Evans','','individual','','The trunks of silk were detained at the customhouse till very lately; first, because of the holidays, and then waiting to get two persons, skilful in silk, to make a valuation of it, in order to ascertain the bounty.','ltr_ben4839.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4840','letter','1772-02-00','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Richard','Price','','individual','','Permit me to thank you, not only on my own Account for the Book itself you have so kindly sent me, but in Behalf of the Publick for Writing it','ltr_ben4840.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4841','letter','1772-04-02','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Wimberley','Jones','','individual','','Your Account of the Governor\'s Treatment of the Assembly & your self, determined me to wait upon him on his Arrival here, as we can not but greatly disapprove his Conduct.','ltr_ben4841.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4842','letter','1772-04-13','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Gushing','','individual','','The Parliament has been employed in the royal marriage bill, and other business; nothing of importance relating to a First published by Sparks.','ltr_ben4842.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4843','letter','1772-04-20','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Jean Baptiste','Le Roy','','individual','','Mr. West, our President, concerning whom you make enquiry, is esteemed a good Antiquarian, but has not distinguish\'d himself in any other Branch of Science.','ltr_ben4843.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4844','letter','1772-05-04','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Priestly','','individual','','I think with you that there cannot be the least Occasion for my explaining your Method of impregnating water with fix\'d air to Messrs. Banks and Solander, as they were present','ltr_ben4844.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4845','letter','1772-05-05','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','I thank you for your Advice about putting back a Fit of the Gout. I shall never attempt such a Thing.','ltr_ben4845.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4846','letter','1772-05-29','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','Dawson','','individual','','Having visited yesterday, as you desired, the powder magazines at Purfleet, in order to see how they may be protected against danger from lightning, I think...','ltr_ben4846.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4847','letter','1772-06-15','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Du Pont','De Nemours','','individual','','I am much obliged to you for introducing me to the Knowledge of M. le Marquis d\'Ecrammeville, who appears a very amiable Man, with an excellent Understanding.','ltr_ben4847.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4848','letter','1772-06-17','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Francis','Maseres','','individual','','I thank you for the pamphlets proposing to establish Life Annuities in Parishes, &c. I think it an excellent one.','ltr_ben4848.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4849','letter','1772-07-14','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','I am just returned from a Journey of near a Month, which has given a new Spring to my Health and Spirits.','ltr_ben4849.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4850','letter','1772-08-12','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Du Pont','De Nemours','','individual','','I am concerned to understand lately that you have never been paid as I expected for the Ephemerides, and therefore I send you three Guineas','ltr_ben4850.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4851','letter','1772-08-17','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','At length we have got rid of Lord Hillsborough, and Lord Dartmouth takes his place, to the great satisfaction of all the friends of America.','ltr_ben4851.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4852','letter','1772-08-19','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','The resolution you have taken to use more exercise is extremely proper; and I hope you will steadily perform it. It is of the greatest importance to prevent diseases, since the cure of them by physic is so very precarious.','ltr_ben4852.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4853','letter','1772-08-19','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','As Lord Hillsborough in fact got nothing out of me, I should rather suppose he threw me away as an orange that would yield no juice, and therefore not worth more squeezing.','ltr_ben4853.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4854','letter','1772-08-22','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Smith','','individual','','I received yours of May 16 with the Box of Books, and have already delivered and forwarded most of them as directed.','ltr_ben4854.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4855','letter','1772-08-22','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Anthony','Benezet','','individual','','I am glad to hear that the disposition against keeping negroes grows more general in North America. Several pieces have been lately printed here against the practice','ltr_ben4855.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4856','letter','1772-08-22','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Bartram','','individual','','I am glad the Rhubarb Seed got safe to hand. I make no doubt of its Thriving well in our Country','ltr_ben4856.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4857','letter','1772-08-22','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Galloway','','individual','','Lord Hillsborough, mortified by the Committee of Council\'s approbation of our grant, in opposition to his report, has resigned.','ltr_ben4857.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4858','letter','1772-09-03','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Gushing','','individual','','Lord Dartmouth, now our American minister, is at present in the country, and will probably not be in town till the season of business comes on. I shall then immediately put the petition into his hands','ltr_ben4858.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4859','letter','1772-09-06','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Huske','','individual','','America is infinitely oblig\'d to you for your continued good Wishes & Schemes for her Advantage : But I am sorry to tell you that she is here become an Object of Jealousy','ltr_ben4859.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4860','letter','1772-09-06','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Walsh','','individual','','Nothing new in the Philosophic Way has occurred here since my last, in which I think I mentioned Dr. Priestly\'s Experiments','ltr_ben4860.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4861','letter','1772-09-19','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Priestley','','individual','','To get over this, my Way is, to divide half a Sheet of Paper by a Line into two Columns ; writing over the one Pro, and over the other Con.','ltr_ben4861.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4862','letter','1772-09-26','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Georgiana','Shipley','','individual','','I LAMENT with you most sincerely the unfortunate end of poor MUNGO. Few squirrels were better accomplished; for he had had a good education, had travelled far, and seen much of the world.','ltr_ben4862.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4863','letter','1772-09-28','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Richard','Price','','individual','','I did not advise him pro or con, but only explain\'d to him my method of judging for myself in doubtful cases, by what I called Prudential Algebra.','ltr_ben4863.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4864','letter','1772-10-07','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Richard','Bache','','individual','','I am surprised to hear that the Dutchman I assisted with 25 Guineas turned out a Rogue; and that Sheets has paid nothing of what I furnished him when here. I am afraid I do not grow wiser as I grow older.','ltr_ben4864.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4865','letter','1772-10-17','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','John','Bartram','','individual','','I hope the Rhubarb you have sown and distributed will be taken care of. There seems to me no doubt of its doing as well with us as in Scotland. Remember that for Use the Root does not come to its Perfection of Power and Virtue in less than Seven Years.','ltr_ben4865.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4866','letter','1772-11-03','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','','Stirling','','individual','','On my Return to Town I found your Favour, with the Schemes of your Lottery, to which I wish Success','ltr_ben4866.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4867','letter','1772-11-03','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','Lord Dartmouth came to town last Week, and had his first Levee on Wednesday, at which I attended. He received me very politely in his Room','ltr_ben4867.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4868','letter','1772-11-03','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Peter','Timothy','','individual','','It is so difficult a matter to obtain anything of the kind, that I think to leave a good Trade in hopes of an Office, is quitting a Certainty for an Uncertainty, and losing Substance for Shadow.','ltr_ben4868.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4869','letter','1772-11-03','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Jonathan','Williams','','individual','','If that should take place, my request is that you would lay out the sum of fifty pounds, lawful money, in bedding or such other furniture as my sister shall think proper to be given the new-married couple','ltr_ben4869.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4870','letter','1772-11-04','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Gushing','','individual','','Lord Dartmouth, our American minister, came to town last week, and held his first levee on Wednesday','ltr_ben4870.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4871','letter','1772-12-02','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Thomas','Gushing','','individual','','A few Days after my leaving your Petition with Lord Dartmouth, his Lordship sent for me to discourse with me upon it.','ltr_ben4871.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4872','letter','1772-12-01','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Deborah','Franklin','','individual','','I am glad to hear you continue so well, and that the Pains in your Side and Head have left you. Eat light Foods, such as Fowls, Mutton, etc., and but little Beef or Bacon, avoid strong Tea, and use what Exercise you can','ltr_ben4872.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4873','letter','1772-12-02','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Joseph','Galloway','','individual','','We must not in the Course of Publick Life expect immediate Approbation and immediate grateful Acknowledgment of our Services. But let us persevere thro\' Abuse and even Injury.','ltr_ben4873.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4874','letter','1772-12-02','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','Abel','James','','individual','','I do not at this Distance understand the Politics of your last Election, why so many of the Members declin\'d the Service, and why yourself and Mr. Fox were omitted','ltr_ben4874.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_ben4875','letter','1772-12-02','London','','ENG','Benjamin','Franklin','','William','Franklin','','individual','','I am persuaded that your Packets were not open\'d at the Office; for tho\' a Secretary of the State has the Power of ordering Letters to be opened, I think it is seldom used but in times of War, Rebellion, or on some great publick Occasion','ltr_ben4875.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'The Writings of Benjamin Franklin Volume V, Albert Henry Smyth, 1906');
